<br>
I'm a necromancer and as an upstanding soldier of Lust for Blood, duelling is part of the package.<br>
<br>
However I am aware that there are some dangers in using DoTs on PCs, and that in some circumstances it can cause exp loss.  I don't want to rain on anyones parade so...<br>
<br>
Is it bad etiquette to use DoTs in a duel?<br>
Is it only appropriate to use them at the beginning?<br>
Is it something that should be agreed beforehand?<br>
And if I shouldn't use themm, am I expected to lifetap people to death while distracting them with witty repartee as my pet bashes them over the head?<br>
<br>
